[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    142[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mAt a conceptual level, a lab outlier detection pipeline has to do two things at once: serve real-time screening for results arriving from the analyzers (low-latency, per-result decisions that gate autoverification and callback), and run longer-window pattern detection for cohort-level and trend-level signals. Under both sits a shared reference data layer (reference ranges, analyte metadata, rule library) and a shared patient-context layer (demographics, recent results, active problems, medications).[K
